observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:

The Municipal Accountant reconcile the inventory records with the inventory report of the Property and Supply Office and draw the necessary adjusting journal entries in the books to correct the affected accounts in the financial statements;
The Property and Supply Officer prepare property cards of all unrecorded PPEs totaling ₱424,966.00 to be included in the RPCPPE;
The Property and Supply Officer complete the details required in all PARs issued and ensure that all property items used in the offices such as IT Equipment and Furniture and Fixtures bear the appropriate property stickers; and
All offices concerned to report/return destroyed/unserviceable property that are no longer needed to the Supply Office for proper disposal, cancellation of PARs and preparation of required reports.

We recommended that:

The Municipal Accountant correct the affected accounts by drawing the appropriate adjusting journal entry;
Henceforth, the Municipal Agriculturist Office coordinate and reconcile with the Municipal Accounting Office on inventory of the biological assets, and periodically provide the Municipal Accounting Office an inventory report for recording purposes;
The Municipal Agriculturist monitor, measure and include in its inventory report the biological transformations of the assets and the results of agricultural activities such as when a swine is born, sold or dies; and
The Municipal Accountant be guided by IPSAS 27 – Agriculture on the proper recognition and measurement of Biological Asset and disclosure in the financial statements.
